{
  "type": "blocks",
  "title": "Ice Blocks",
  "summaries": [
    "<b>Ice Blocks</b> are a common block type found alongside Snow Blocks in the Snow and Ice biomes. They can be mined with a pickaxe or drill. Ice Blocks have low friction, causing a player walking over them to slide when stopping or changing directions. This effect can be mitigated by equipping Ice Skates or other accessories crafted from them.",
    "Ice Blocks can be converted into three other variants via the spread of biomes:",
    "<ul><li>Corruption spreads onto Ice to create <b>Purple Ice Blocks</b></li><li>Crimson spreads onto Ice to create <b>Red Ice Blocks</b></li><li>Hallow spreads onto Ice to create <b>Pink Ice Blocks</b></li></ul>",
    "These will also spread their respective biomes."
  ],
